description:
&lt;p&gt;If you are energetic, motivated to try new ways of working in a large multi-disciplinary team, have skills in assessment, engagement and positive risk taking, and then please consider applying.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Medway and Swale Crisis Resolution Home Treatment Team is looking for a new CPN/Occupational Therapist(Band 5) to join their team providing a responsive assessment and home treatment service to those experiencing an acute crisis in the community. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be expected to work collaboratively with service users, carers and other professionals, offering an alternative to admission across the areas of Medway&lt;br /&gt;and Swale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Car business Insurance is desirable and you should be prepared to work shifts including nights, bank holidays and weekends, and be able to undertake PMVA training and support persons waiting for assessment in the designated place of safety.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Medway/Swale CRHTT Manager- Andrew Fullager on 01634 968460&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Andrew.fullagar@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
